<subSubSection pageId="37" pageNumber="38" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1437,153,683]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,548,575]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Comments.</emphasis>
Compared with the other species that have a complete posterior transverse carina, short notauli, and closed areolet, head strongly transverse and frontal orbits with yellow marks not reaching level of anterior ocellus, unlike in 
<emphasis box="[351,817,621,647]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Humala" authorityYear="2019" box="[351,486,621,647]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Orthocentrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="khalaimi">O. khalaimi</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[497,644,621,647]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Orthocentrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montanus">O. montanus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Humala" authorityYear="2019" box="[655,817,621,647]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Orthocentrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montezuma">O. montezuma</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Humala" authorityYear="2019" box="[871,985,621,647]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Orthocentrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sierrae">
<emphasis box="[871,985,621,647]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">O. sierrae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; subocular sulcus strongly bent towards occiput and basal flagellomere comparatively short, unlike in 
<emphasis box="[844,1018,657,683]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Humala" authorityYear="2019" box="[844,1014,657,683]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Orthocentrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tlaxcalensis">O. tlaxcalensis</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
